cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.RO, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with non-rigid structure-from-motion (NRSfM) for multiple non-rigid objects, which is a problem in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a spatio-temporal representation for the 3D non-rigid deformations and trajectories, which involves both spatial and temporal dimensions, making cs.GR (Graphics) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also uses optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper proposes a unified framework that jointly segments and reconstructs multiple non-rigid objects, which could involve machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
